# Mini Brief

Design a parking lot using object-oriented principles...

This is a play ground for what you have learned try and practically apply.

- Control flow
- Classes
- Methods
- Lists, Array
- Unit tests
- Interfaces

## Assumptions

- The parking lot can hold motorcycles, cars and vans
- The parking lot has motorcycle spots, car spots and large spots
- A motorcycle can park in any spot
- A car can park in a single regular spot, or a large spot
- A van can park in a large spot, or it will take up 3 regular spots
- All vehicles will try and park in their allotted spaces first

## Specifications

Here are a few methods that you should be able to run:

- Tell us how many spots are remaining
- Tell us how many total spots are in the parking lot
- Tell us when the parking lot is full
- Tell us when the parking lot is empty
- Tell us when certain spots are full e.g. when all motorcycle spots are taken
- Tell us how many spots vans are taking up